    Twitter, as a micro-blogging system, allows users to publish tweets of up to 140 characters in length to tell others what they are doing, what they are thinking, or what is happening around them.
    Over the past few years, Twitter has become very popular.
    According to the latest Twitter entry in Wikipedia, the number of Twitter users has climbed to 190 million and the number of tweets published on Twitter every day is over 65 million1.
    As a result of the rapidly increasing number of tweets, mining people&#8217;s sentiments expressed in tweets has attracted more and more attention.
